d business today.This text breaks new ground in introducing organizational psychology from a cross cultural perspective. It provides a foundational overview of the current major theories in organizational psychology, and illuminates the impact of cultural differences on organizational dynamics. It also makes available specific research concerning our current understandings of how these dynamics play out in particular regions and countries, such as autocratic versus democratic leadership styles in Africa and Europe or conflict management in Asia. The volume offers a welcome introduction to the topic to those in industrial/organizational psychology, international relations and management, and international business/MBA programs focusing on international issues.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aIntercultural communication. 0aOrganizational behaviorvCross-cultural studies. 0aPersonnel managementvCross-cultural studies. 0aPsychology, IndustrialvCross-cultural studies. 7aPSYCHOLOGY / General.2bisacsh  aThis.  abreaks.  across.  acultural.  acurrent.  adifferences.  adynamics.  afoundational.  afrom.  aground.  ailluminates.  aimpact.  aintroducing.  amajor.  aorganizational.  aoverview.  aperspective.  aprovides.  apsychology.  atext.  atheories.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831107064440 cprintz978081474006440uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9780814786581.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814786581423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814786581/original  a978-3-11-070644-4  New York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL 